      <h3><a name="2007-02-25" href="#2007-02-25">
          <font color="#660000">2007-02-25</font></a></h3>
   	

	<div class="posts">
    <a name="7562779844911108387"></a>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><h2><cite cite="http://lifehacker.com/software/inspiration/find-inspiration-from-historical-accomplishments-239452.php">At My Age, It&rsquo;s Time To Get Busy</cite></h2>
<p><a href="http://lifehacker.com/software/inspiration/find-inspiration-from-historical-accomplishments-239452.php">Find inspiration from historical accomplishments - Lifehacker</a>.&nbsp; Thanks to this Lifehacker item, I learned about the "<A href="http://www.museumofconceptualart.com/accomplished/">Things Other People Accomplished</A>" page and&nbsp;the effort to catalog accomplishments of&nbsp;various kinds.</p>
<p>At my recent-birthday age, </p>
<blockquote>
<p>The English experimentalist William Crookes began investigating radioactivity and invented a device for detecting alpha particles. </p>
<p>French President Charles de Gaulle, who resigned 12 years earlier out of impatience with party politics, made a political comeback.</p></blockquote>
<hr>

<p><small>This post is also my way of testing whether I have now banished the extra blank lines that the new Blogger has been adding to my posts, probably because of a new/old setting that has unexpected behavior.&nbsp; I don't know whether that is something "worthless, pathetic or dubious" that I should submit.&nbsp; Perhaps it goes along with my being of an age that I still put extra spaces after the periods in sentences and I much prefer the layout of my sentences that way.</small></p>
<p><small><strong>update 2007&ndash;02&ndash;25T19:24Z</strong> Well, it was a &ldquo;new&rdquo; Blogger setting, and now everything on my main page has the expected spacing between paragraphs.&nbsp; Of course, the archive pages of earlier articles are not republished: I never republish the site as I make changes over time, and you can see what it was like when it wasn&rsquo;t working on the just-previous post <a href="http://orcmid.com/blog/2007/02/peter-naur-science-for-computer-science.asp">here</a>.&nbsp; Now all I have to figure out is how BlogJet has stopped allowing me to explicitly set the title of my posts.&nbsp; (And to get it to stop making an automatic link every time I type &ldquo;BlogJet&rdquo; I am increasingly tempted to try out the Microsoft Live Writer blog tool.)</small></p><div class="bjtags">Tags:  <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/Lifehacker">Lifehacker</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid">orcmid</a>, <a rel="tag" href="http://technorati.com/tag/accomplishment">accomplishment</a></div><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </p>
